Interface IQueryResult

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.lang.AutoCloseable

    public interface IQueryResult
extends java.lang.AutoCloseable

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void close()
      Closes the query result and releases all resources used by the query which include the data returned by the query.
      boolean hasNext()
      Returns true if the query result has more data either as rows or items or false the query result does not have more data.
      boolean isClosed()
      Returns whether an instance has been closed or not with all underlying resources released.
      java.util.List toList()
      Returns an instance of List containing all the data returned by the query.

    • Method Detail

      • close

        void close()
           throws TeamRepositoryException
        Closes the query result and releases all resources used by the query which include the data returned by the query. After invocation the query result is useless and the invocation of any of the of the api will result in an exception being thrown.
        Specified by:
        close in interface java.lang.AutoCloseable
        Throws:
        TeamRepositoryException

      • hasNext

        boolean hasNext()
                throws TeamRepositoryException
        Returns true if the query result has more data either as rows or items or false the query result does not have more data. It is expected that this will be used before calling any of the api that returns data
        Returns:
        true if the query result has more data.
        Throws:
        TeamRepositoryException - indicating that something failed while attempting to determine whether there is a next element.

      • toList
